      <item>
        <key>Catalogue Pattern.Patient Requirements</key>
        <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CT Virtual Colonography&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;---------------------------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At least 7 DAYS before the appointment:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;---------------------------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If you have &lt;strong&gt;NOT &lt;/strong&gt;received a phone call from the Diagnostic Imaging Department please contact the hospital where your appointment is scheduled for information on where to pick up your CT COLONOGRAPHY BOWEL PREPARATION KIT.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Weight:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to the weight capacity of the Diagnostic Imaging equipment, if your weight is more than 400 pounds, please contact the Diagnostic Imaging site where you are booked to ensure you are scheduled at an appropriate site.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Childcare:&lt;/strong&gt; Arrange childcare or bring family member or a friend to stay with children during your procedure. For safety reasons, children are not permitted in procedure rooms and cannot be left unattended.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Support Person:&lt;/strong&gt; Arrange for a family member or friend to accompany you to your appointment to provide the support you may need, including language translation.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Pregnancy Status: &lt;/strong&gt;You CANNOT have this exam if there is ANY possibility you might be pregnant.&amp;nbsp; Be sure you discuss this with your doctor before booking this exam.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Diabetes:&lt;/strong&gt; Patients taking DIABETES MEDICATIONS should consult their diabetes care provider for medication review and possible adjustment while on clear fluid diet and/or during fasting.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For patients with DIABETES using Insulin Pump Therapy at home, please review “Guidelines for Managing Pump during Radiologic Procedures” at www.ipumpit.ca &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Continuous Glucose Monitoring Devices (CGMD):&lt;/strong&gt; If you currently wear a CGMD and the device is in the area that is going to be imaged, it is recommended that you remove the device prior to your appointment. If you choose to wear your device during your scan and it is in the area that is going to be imaged you will be required to complete finger prick readings simultaneous to your CGMD readings after the imaging to ensure your monitor continues to operate as expected.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; AHS will not cover the cost of a replacement CGMD should these preparation instructions not be adhered to. If you are unsure whether you need to remove your device or cannot adhere to this portion of the preparation instructions please contact the Diagnostic Imaging Department directly.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Please let the staff know that you have a CGMD when you arrive at your appointment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;----------------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 DAYS before the appointment:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;----------------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow instructions in the CT COLONOGRAPHY BOWEL PREPARATION KIT. The contents of your preparation kit is determined based on your kidney function.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;BRING to the appointment:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Healthcare card&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Picture identification&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Your green sleeve that includes your Goals of Care (GOC) Designation Order form that was completed with your physician (if you have one)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Med List:&lt;/strong&gt; A list of medications you are currently taking so we can double check to see if any of them would interfere with the exam&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Any medication with you that you may need to take during your time in Diagnostic Imaging&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Your eye glasses and hearing aid(s)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Your mobility aid/device&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Patients with DIABETES - insulin and glucometer&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;--------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DO NOT bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;--------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Remove and leave at home any jewelry or piercings that are near to or cover the area being examined.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Leave valuables at home as you may not have a secured space to place your items during your appointment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Consider limiting the number of items you bring to the appointment.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;----------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AT the appointment:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;----------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; You will be asked to change into a hospital gown – it will be provided to you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The exam requires a very small flexible tube to be passed into rectum to allow air or other gas to be pumped into the colon. The air distends (inflates) the bowel and smooths out any wrinkles or folds to allow better view of the walls of the colon.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Your appointment will take about 60 minutes in total; the exam takes 15-20 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-----------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AFTER the appointment: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-----------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; You may NOT be able to resume your activities after the exam because the preparation can continue to require you to have frequent bowel movements.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; You may be given instructions after exam (if applicable).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Results will be provided to the ordering doctor in 3 to 5 business days and will also appear in MyAHS Connect.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;-&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Follow the instructions your doctor gave you to discuss the test results.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
      </item>
