      <item>
        <key>Catalogue Pattern.Ordering Clinician Instructions</key>
        <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IP:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DIET: &lt;/strong&gt;2 day bowel preparation is required. Diagnostic Imaging will provide information when procedure is scheduled.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IV ACCESS&lt;/strong&gt;: Adults may require IV access.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MEDICATION:&lt;/strong&gt; Patient will receive either oral Buscopan (as part of the bowel preparation kit) or IV Buscopan or Glucagon (at the time of the exam) to improve bowel distention for imaging purposes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;The patient may take regular medications during bowel preparation. If the patient is on Insulin, please instruct patient about Insulin dose as appropriate. &amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMUNICATION: &lt;/strong&gt;Notify department if translation services are required. Notify department if patient is on dialysis.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PATIENT ATTIRE:&lt;/strong&gt; Patient dressed in hospital gown only. Patient to bring eye glasses and hearing aids.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Remove any metallic objects from area of scan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AMB:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DIET:&lt;/strong&gt; 2 day bowel preparation is required. Diagnostic Imaging will provide information when procedure is scheduled. The patient is required to pick up preparation kit prior to appointment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MEDICATION:&lt;/strong&gt; Patient will receive either oral Buscopan (as part of the bowel preparation kit) or IV Buscopan or Glucagon (at the time of the exam) to improve bowel distention for imaging purposes. The patient may take regular medications during bowel preparation. If the patient is on Insulin, please instruct patient about Insulin dose as appropriate. &amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMUNICATION:&lt;/strong&gt; Notify department if translation services are required.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PATIENT ATTIRE: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Patient to bring eye glasses and hearing aids.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Remove any metallic objects from abdominal area.&lt;/p&gt;</value>
      </item>
      <item>
        <key>Catalogue Pattern.Synonyms</key>
        <value>&lt;p&gt;301000; CT Colon; CT Virtual Colonoscopy&lt;/p&gt;</value>
